Deployment (Deploy) is one of the most important concepts in software engineering, AI, web development, cloud computing, and DevOps.

Think of it like this:

Building = Cooking the food 🍳
Deploying = Serving the food to customers 🍽️

You may write excellent code on your computer, but until you deploy it, nobody else can use it.

What is Deployment?

Deployment is the process of moving your application, website, AI model, or software from your local computer to a server (or cloud platform) so that users can access it through the Internet or a private network.

In simple words,

Deployment = Making your software available for users.

Real Life Example

Imagine you own a restaurant.

Step 1

You cook food in your kitchen.

Only you can eat it.

↓

Step 2

You move the food to the restaurant counter.

Now customers can buy it.

That movement is called

Deployment

Exactly the same happens in software.

